Language: Ilocano
Language code: ilo
Lines: orth orth-seg gloss translat
Author: James Blackburn, Kazuki Shintani
Date: April 7, 2016
Source a: Rubino, Carl. Reference grammar of Ilocano. Diss. University of California, Santa Barbara, 1997.


######################################
######### ADJECTIVES #################
######################################

# Week 4
# Adjectives as modifiers to nouns
Source: a:122
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {adjectives}
Kayatko      ti      nalabaga  a   balay
Kayat=ko     ti      na-labaga a   balay
want=ERG.1SG CORE.SG ADJ-red   LIG house
`I want the red house`

# Adjectives may either precede or follow the noun
# they qualify, linked by the ligature (ng)a. When
# used to distinguish, they normally follow the noun.
# Week 4
# Adjectives as nouns, grammar concept betted, exact
# words are not betted
Source: a:139
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {adjectives}
Kayatko      ti      balay a   nalabaga
Kayat=ko     ti      balay a   na-labaga
want=ERG.1SG CORE.SG house LIG ADJ-red
`I want the red house`


