######### NEGATION ###################
######################################

# a simple sentential negation with aux 'di' without any abs/erg cases
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {negation}
Di  n-ag-laylay ti      sabong
di  n-ag-laylay ti      sabong
Neg PF-I-wilt   CORE.SG flower.ABS
`The flower didn't wilt'

# a sentential negation with aux 'di' with any abs enclitic
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {negation}
Diak        nagsangit
di=ak       n-ag-sangit
Neg=ABS.1sg PF-I-cry
`I did not cry'

# negation 'di' is not for negating NP-only
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: f
Phenomena: {negation}
Di  ti      lalaki
di  ti      lalaki
Neg CORE.SG boy
`Not the boy'

# in negation, a case needs to agree between the subjet (absolutive) and the intransitive verb
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: f
Phenomena: {case}
Diko        nagsangit
di=ko       n-ag-sangit
Neg=ERG.1sg PF-I-cry
`I did not cry'

# negation with transitive verb sentense
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {negation}
Diko        nakita   ti      lalaki
di=ko       na-kita  ti      lalaki
Neg=ERG.1sg PF.T-see CORE.SG boy
`I didn't see the boy'

# negation with transitive verb sentense, but wrong case (needs ERG, but given ABS)
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: f
Phenomena: {case}
Diak        nakita   ti      lalaki
di=ak       na-kita  ti      lalaki
Neg=ABS.1sg PF.T-see CORE.SG boy
`I didn't see the boy'


